# Git Workflow

## Branch Strategy
- `main` — production only, never commit directly
- `staging` — pre-production, QA environment
- `dev` — active development base branch
- Feature branches: `feature/short-description`
- Bug fixes: `fix/short-description`
- Hotfixes: `hotfix/short-description`

## What You CAN Do
- `git status` — always safe
- `git diff` — always safe
- `git log` — always safe
- `git checkout -b branch-name` — safe, but confirm branch name first
- `git stash` — safe, but notify the user

## What You CANNOT Do
- `git commit` — user commits manually, always
- `git push` — user pushes manually, always
- `git merge` — ask user to confirm before suggesting
- `git rebase` — never suggest without explicit request
- `git reset --hard` — never, unless user explicitly asks with full awareness

## Rollback Protocol
If something breaks and rollback is needed:
1. Run `git status` and `git diff` and show the user
2. Suggest the rollback command — do NOT run it
3. Wait for user confirmation before any destructive action

## Commit Message Format (for suggestions only)
```
type(scope): short description

- bullet of what changed
- bullet of what changed
```
Types: `feat`, `fix`, `refactor`, `chore`, `docs`, `style`, `test`
